How to run:

Required packages:
   -ant
   -mysql-server

Steps:
   -Clone repository into home directory (otherwise default paths will be broken), creating ~/DICE.
   -Set up MySQL for jgossip:
      -Use dbsetup/create_database.sql to create the forum_db database.
      -Run install.sql, and then initload.sql on forum_db to initialize jgossip database.
         -eg. sudo mysql -p forum_db < install.sql
   -Set up PATH for ibm-java:
      -You can add the following to your ~/.bashrc:

if [[ -d "$HOME/DICE/ibm-java/jre/bin" && ! $PATH =~ $HOME/DICE/ibm-java/jre/bin ]]
then
#    echo "Adding jre bin"
    PATH="$HOME/DICE/ibm-java/jre/bin:$PATH"
fi

if [[ -d "$HOME/DICE/ibm-java/bin" && ! $PATH =~ $HOME/DICE/ibm-java/bin ]]
then
#    echo "Adding ibm bin"
    PATH="$HOME/DICE/ibm-java/bin:$PATH"
fi

   -Build jgossip (from in ~/DICE) with: ant -buildfile jgossip/build.xml dist -Ddeploy_env=default
   -Update src/taint/GeneralTracker.aj, DBCPTaint.aj so that logfiles are created in correct home directory.
   -Do AspectJ weaving to produce weaved jgossip.war by running jgossipaspect.sh
   -Start tomcat (port 8686 currently) with: JAVA_HOME=~/DICE/ibm-java ~/DICE/tomcat/bin/startup.sh
   -Go to localhost:8686/manager/html (username: user, password: user)
   -Deploy ~/DICE/jgossip.war (produced by jgossipaspect.sh)
   -Go to localhost:8686/jgossip/jgossip
   -jGossip should run, and taint tracking logs should be produced
   -You can stop tomcat with: ~/DICE/tomcat/bin/shutdown.sh
